FBIS4-65571 "drweu097_n_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 NORDIC COUNTRIES Denmark Government Rejects UN Request for Troops in Rwanda Government Rejects UN Request for Troops in Rwanda LD1805131594 Stockholm Radio Sweden in Swedish 1030 GMT 18 May 94 LD1805131594 Stockholm Radio Sweden Swedish BFN [Text] Denmark is saying no to a UN request to contribute personnel and equipment to the UN peacekeeping force in Rwanda. The Danish foreign minister says Denmark is already contributing UN troops at other sites. In addition, he questions whether the United Nations has a reasonable chance to carry out the task in Rwanda. The United Nations has also asked Sweden to support the UN force in Rwanda. According to UN diplomats, Sweden could contribute engineering troops, helicopters, and hospitals.
